column1: ""description"": ""Twin Pine Manor is a spacious mansion with nine luxurious guest rooms, all with Jacuzzi tubs and fireplaces. We offer a romantic countryside retreat-setting for bed and breakfast guests. Our B&B is located in the heart of Pennsylvania Dutch Amish Country, with convenient access to Lititz, Lancaster City, Bird-in-Hand, Manheim, Strasburg, and Intercourse. "",

""reviewBody"": ""My husband and I needed to get away from it all,  recharge and spend some much needed quality time together. I surprised him with an overnight trip to Twin Pine Manor. It was our first visit. This place is immaculate. Right away I was regretting not booking it for 2 nights. One was just not enough. We had the Amaryllis Suite . This room is on the first floor. It has a super comfy Queen bed and a hot tub. The hot tub fits 2 perfectly. They even supply the bubbles and 2 soft comfy robes! Our room was right next to the kitchen which was very convenient and made no noise at all.  We explored the Manor and the grounds...AMAZING! There is a beautiful deck to sit out on with a country view which we had access to from our room. Parking for our suite was right outside which made it easy to transport our bags and cooler. We chose to have our breakfast delivered to our room. It's the first time we ever had room service..how cool! Thank you Brenda for the delicious breakfast and your kindness and hospitality. The whole place is just so cozy..and clean. The chocolate chip cookies that were complimentary in our room were the best ever! My husband fell asleep after using the hot tub so I ate his! I can't even begin to tell you how relaxing this little trip was. Just one night helped us feel that closeness again and has given us more happy memories to add to the 18 years we have together already. We have already booked our next visit and I can't wait! If you're thinking about staying here just DO IT! You won't regret it. The Devine's give it 5 stars!"",

""reviewBody"": ""This place is amazing!!!  We were looking for somewhere to elope.  When I found Twin Pine Manor online and saw the grounds, I knew this was the place.  When I originally called to ask if it would be okay to get married there, they told me they do not allow weddings.  But when I explained it would only be us and an efficient they said okay and we said I Do! The keepers were amazing, the rooms were great.  Their food was delicious.  The grounds were so pretty.  Their experience will be in our hearts forever!  We are definitely going back again.  We stayed in the Alpine room and will try the tower next time.  Highly suggest Twin Pines Manor.  We have been to many B & B's and this place stands above the rest in many ways. Sherri and Michael"",

IP.CodProduto AS PROD_CPROD, IP.DescPro AS PROD_XPROD, IP.Qtde AS PROD_QCOM, IP.QTRIB AS PROD_QTRIB, IP.UTRIB AS PROD_UTRIB,
IP.Unidade AS PROD_UCOM, IP.ValUni AS PROD_VUNCOM, IP.VUNTRIB AS PROD_VUNTRIB, IP.Total AS PROD_VPROD, IP.pICMS AS IMPOSTO_ICMS_PICMS,
IP.vFrete AS PROD_VFRETE, 0.00 AS PROD_VSEG, IP.vDesc AS PROD_VDESC, 0.00 AS PROD_VOUTRO, PRO.CodOrigem AS IMPOSTO_ICMS_ORIG,
IP.CodTributacao AS IMPOSTO_ICMS_CST, PRO.NCM AS PROD_NCM, PRO.CodGrupo, PRO.MedidaInt, PRO.MedidaExt, PRO.MedidaAlt, PRO.CodEan,
FROM         dbo.Pedidos AS P INNER JOIN
dbo.ItensPedido AS IP ON P.NroPedido = IP.NroPedido LEFT OUTER JOIN
dbo.EQCLID AS C ON P.CodCliente = C.CodCli LEFT OUTER JOIN
dbo.Cidades AS CID ON C.CODCID = CID.CodCid CROSS JOIN
dbo.Empresa AS E LEFT OUTER JOIN
dbo.Cidades AS CIDEMP ON E.CodCid = CIDEMP.CodCid INNER JOIN
dbo.Produtos AS PRO ON IP.CodProduto = PRO.CodProduto LEFT OUTER JOIN
dbo.TipoOperacao AS TPO ON P.CodTpo = TPO.CodOperacao
